         <div type="translation" resp="part:argr">
 	<p rend="stanza" n="1">The well-mannered one who, with joy, has particular devotion to Mahādeva three times <supplied reason="explanation">per day</supplied> always benefits from the Companion <supplied reason="explanation">Śiva</supplied>, being in <supplied reason="subaudible">His</supplied> control.</p>
	<p rend="stanza" n="2">Time, which the wise men here exhaustively starting by years and months; gold, which in <supplied reason="subaudible">this</supplied> world variously ...; the son who is born from the union of spouses ... and when ... the senses ...; Viṣṇu, his wife <supplied reason="subaudible">and</supplied> their son, the three, ... here ... </p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
           <p>The text is incomplete. Traces of the very top of a 7th line are visible on the photos. Unusual cross marks occupy the space between lines 1 and 2. Extra space is left open between stanzas 1 and 2.</p>
         </div>
